Paul Gauguin's paintings in Tahiti will be [exposed at the Tate
Modern](http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/standard/article-23825760-tates-gaugin-
show-aims-to-explode-myths-of-tahiti.do) in London in September 2010.
_Mercury_ at Philosophy of Science Portal wonders whether [his paintings were
a true reflection of life in
Tahiti](http://philosophyofscienceportal.blogspot.com/2010/04/paul-
gauguinself-publicisttwister-of.html).

